main event: Five white and orange objects appeared similar to an explosion and back together again, flashing lights, and seemed to fade as going through a cloud over Columbus, Nebraska on 29 July 1955 for five to six minutes.
interesting points: The sighting involved five white and orange objects that appeared to behave erratically, similar to an explosion and then coming back together again.
The objects appeared as flashing lights and seemed to fade as they moved through a cloud.
The source of the observation was civilian, and it lasted for a relatively long duration of five to six minutes.
The sighting was considered semi-fantastic in nature, and the failure to meet investigation criteria led to its resolution as UNKNOWN and the forwarding of the report to ATIC.
Despite the conclusion of unknown, the report noted the possibility of the objects being balloons, aircraft, or astronomical phenomena.
